Source: www.unsplash.comCapital Craft Beer Festival is setting out to unite beer and music lovers in the Pretoria National Botanical Gardens. The festival will not only feature craft brewers and a diverse selection of food, but also see some of the best local artists South Africa’s music scene has to offer.  This year's line-up does not disappoint - from stalwarts to classics to newcomers. From rock to blues to folk to pop to swing. From Afrikaans to English and everything in between.  Gather your gang and come and enjoy good food, good times and good friends! Festival detailsThe artist lineup at the festival includes Karen Zoid, Bongeziwe Mabandla, Aking, Dan Patlansky, Bad Peter, Georgetown & The Moonies, Pedro Barbosa, The Man Motels and more. Image supplied: The artist lineup for the Capital Craft Beer FestivalBrewers include Agar’s Brewery, Cape Brewing Company, Devil’s Peak Beer Company, Jack Black’s Brewing Company, Mad Giant, Mohope, The Kennel Brewery, Tokolazi Craft Beer and more. The event will take place on 18 June at the Pretoria National Botanical Gardens from 10am to 6pm. Tickets are limited for R250 and can be purchased here.